 <p>
  <b>Mresize</b>
  (
  <em>matrix</em>
  ;
  <em>m</em>
  ;
  <em>n</em>
  )
 </p>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <span class="b0">[</span>
   1; 2; 3
   <span class="b0">|</span>
   4; 5; 6
   <span class="b0">|</span>
   7; 8; 9
   <span class="b0">]</span>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">6</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">7</span>
     <span class="td">8</span>
     <span class="td">9</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates a general type matrix
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>mresize</b>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ; 2; 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">6</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - resizes to a general type as well
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">6</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - the original matrix has changed
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>diagonal</b>
   ( 3; 5 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates a diagonal type matrix
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>mresize</b>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ; 2; 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">5</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
