 <p>
  <b>Mfill</b>
  (
  <em>matrix</em>
  ;
  <em>value</em>
  )
 </p>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>matrix</b>
   ( 2; 3 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates an empty matrix A
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>mfill</b>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ; 1 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - fills A with ones and assigns the result to B
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   <sub>1,2</sub>
   = 2
  </span>
  - changes a single value in B which references A
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - A has also changed
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>L</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>mfill</b>
   (
   <b>ltriang</b>
   ( 4 ) ; 2 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - special matrices are filled only inside the designated area
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
 <p>
  <b>Fill_Row</b>
  (
  <em>matrix</em>
  ;
  <em>row index</em>
  ;
  <em>value</em>
  )
 </p>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>matrix</b>
   ( 3; 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates a general matrix
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>fill</b>
   <sub>row</sub>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ; 2; 1 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - fills the 2-nd row with value of 1
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>L</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>utriang</b>
   ( 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates an upper triangular matrix
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <span class="cond">$Repeat</span>
   {
   <b>fill</b>
   <sub>row</sub>
   (
   <b>
    <var>L</var>
   </b>
   ;
   <var>k</var>
   ;
   <var>k</var>
   )
   <span class="cond">for</span>
   <var>k</var>
   = 1...
   <b>n</b>
   <sub>rows</sub>
   (
   <b>
    <var>L</var>
   </b>
   ) } =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - fills all rows
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>L</var>
   </b>
   =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">2</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">3</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">4</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - only the designated area to the type (the upper triangle) is filled
 </p>
 <p>
 </p>
 <p>
  <b>Fill_Col</b>
  (
  <em>matrix</em>
  ;
  <em>column index</em>
  ;
  <em>value</em>
  )
 </p>
 <hr/>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>matrix</b>
   ( 3; 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - creates a general matrix
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>fill</b>
   <sub>col</sub>
   (
   <b>
    <var>A</var>
   </b>
   ; 2; 1 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">1</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - fills the 2nd column with value of 1
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <b>
    <var>B</var>
   </b>
   =
   <b>symmetric</b>
   ( 4 )  =
   <span class="matrix">
    <span class="tr">
     <span class="td">
     </span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">0</span>
     <span class="td">
     </span>
    </span>
    <span class="tr">
